english_text: Bakan naa ni Matiu 12:7, Fritz Tillmann ati Ludwig Thimme tumọ rẹ̀ gẹgẹ bi “tumọsi” [es·tinʹ].Fritz Tillmann and Ludwig Thimme similarly render it “mean” [es·tinʹ] at Matthew 12:7.jw2019

yoruba_text: Lẹ́yìn tí mo sìn ní Uganda fún sáà kan, mo dé DaresSalaam, tí í ṣe olú ìlú Tanganyika, níbẹ̀rẹ̀ ọdún 1956
english_text: After serving in Uganda for some time, I arrived early in 1956 in DaresSalaam, the capital of Tanganyika.

yoruba_text: Bakan naa ni Matiu 12:7, Fritz Tillmann ati Ludwig Thimme tumọ rẹ̀ gẹgẹ bi “tumọsi” [es·tinʹ]
english_text: Fritz Tillmann and Ludwig Thimme similarly render it “mean” [es·tinʹ] at Matthew 12:7.

yoruba_text: Awọn ẹkọ ipilẹṣẹ awọn eto-ajọ Protẹstanti ti jọra pẹlu awọn Ṣọọṣi Katoliki debi pe ọpọ awọn onworan lè fi tirọruntirọrun lo ọ̀rọ̀ ilẹ Andes naa: “Esla misma cholita con otra pollera” (Ọdọmọbinrin ibilẹ kan-naa ni, sikẹẹti rẹ̀ ni o yàtọ̀)
english_text: The basic doctrines of the Protestant organizations are so similar to those of the Catholic Church that many observers could easily use the Andean saying: “Esla misma cholita con otra pollera” (It is the same little Indian woman with a different skirt).

yoruba_text: The Court of Appeal at DaresSalaam, Tanzania’s highest court, unanimously found impermissible the actions of a school board that expelled five students and suspended another 122 for refusing to sing the national anthem
english_text: Es3:2-4 —Kí ló ṣeé ṣe kó fà á tí Módékáì fi kọ̀ láti tẹrí ba fún Hámánì?Es3:2-4 —Why might Mordecai have refused to bow down to Haman?jw2019

yoruba_text: Ní ìlú DaresSalaam, Ilé Ẹjọ́ Kòtẹ́milọ́rùn tó ga jù lọ lórílẹ̀-èdè Tanzania fẹnu kò pé àwọn kò fara mọ́ ohun tí àwọn aláṣẹ ilé ìwé kan ṣe bí wọ́n ṣe lé akẹ́kọ̀ọ́ márùn-ún kúrò níléèwé tí wọ́n sì ní kí àwọn méjìlélọ́gọ́fà [122] yòókù ṣì lọ máa gbé ilé wọn ná torí pé wọn ò kọ orin orílẹ̀-èdè
english_text: The Court of Appeal at DaresSalaam, Tanzania’s highest court, unanimously found impermissible the actions of a school board that expelled five students and suspended another 122 for refusing to sing the national anthem.

yoruba_text: Es3:2-4 —Kí ló ṣeé ṣe kó fà á tí Módékáì fi kọ̀ láti tẹrí ba fún Hámánì
english_text: Es3:2-4 —Why might Mordecai have refused to bow down to Haman?

yoruba_text: Èyí mú kí n jẹ́jẹ̀ẹ́ pé mi ò ní bá à wọn tó ń sọ èdèEsanda nǹkan kan pọ̀, mi ò sì ni fẹ́ ẹnikẹ́ni tó bá jẹ́ ọmọ ìpínlẹ̀ Edo lá él áé.
english_text: So I vowed that I would have nothing to do with anyone who spoke the Esanlanguage and that I would never marry anyone from Edo State.

yoruba_text: Àmọ́ ọmọ ìpínlẹ̀ Edo ni bà bá mi, èdèEsanni wọ́n sì ń sọ.
english_text: My father's family, however, is from Edo State and speaks the Esanlanguage.

yoruba_text: Wọ́n máa ń gbé à wọn à pilẹ̀kọ kan tó dá lórí Bíbélì já de nínú ìwé ìròyìn Ararat, à mọ́ wọ́n tún máa ń sọ̀rọ̀ lórí béèyàn ṣe lè fi ewé, egbòogi à tà wọn nǹkan à dá yébá míì ṣe ìwòsàn, wọ́n sì tún máa ń sọ̀rọ̀ nípa èdè tuntun kan tó ń jẹ́Esperanto.
english_text: Ararat magazine published Biblical articles but also articles on such topics as natural cures and the newly invented language Esperanto.

yoruba_text: Ninu iwọnyi, Esperanto ti ni ipa tító bi julọ nito ri pe nkan bi 10,000,000 awọn eniyan ti kọ́ ọ lati igba iṣẹda rẹ̀ ni ọdun 1887.
english_text: Of these, Esperantohas had the most impact because about 10,000,000 people have learned it since its creation in the year 1887.
